            "body": "Not sure I can reproduce?\n\n```\n# cython: annotation_typing = False\n\ndef f(a: int, b: float) -> None:\n    pass\n\nprint(f.__annotations__)\nimport inspect\nprint(inspect.signature(f))\nprint(f(b\"not an int\", \"not a float\"))  # just confirm that annotation typing is off\n```\n\ngives\n\n```\n{'a': 'int', 'b': 'float', 'return': 'None'}\n(a: 'int', b: 'float') -> 'None'\nNone\n```\n\nso as far as I can tell, `annotation_typing` doesn't affect this. Do you have a more specific example?",
